HEADWORD: Inurbane
<hw>In`ur*bane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inurbanus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Urbane</er>.]</ety>
<def>Uncivil; unpolished; rude. Opposite of <ant>urbane</ant>.</def>
<au>M. Arnold.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>In`ur*bane"ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>In`ur*bane"ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

